## Tiered Validation (Ralph Backpressure)

Use fast feedback loops during development, full validation before PR.

### After Each Code Change (Tier 1 - Immediate, <5s)

```bash
npx tsc --noEmit  # Type check only, catches most issues fast
```

### After Completing a Component/Feature (Tier 2 - Fast, <30s)

```bash
pnpm lint --max-warnings 0      # Lint check
pnpm test -- --run --reporter=dot  # Quick test run
```

### Before Creating PR (Tier 3 - Full, MANDATORY)

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm lint
pnpm typecheck || npx tsc --noEmit
pnpm test || echo "No tests"
pnpm build
```

**DO NOT skip Tier 3 before PR.** Fast tiers are for iteration speed, not completeness.

## Browser Testing: Functional vs Visual

**CRITICAL:** Use the right approach based on what you're verifying.

| Testing Type | Method | Use For |
|--------------|--------|---------|
| **Functional** | `take_snapshot` / DOM inspection | Button exists, text appears, form works |
| **Visual** | `take_screenshot` | Layout, colors, styling, animations |

**Common mistake:** Taking screenshots to verify behavior. Screenshots are images—you cannot parse them to check if a button exists. Use snapshot/DOM for functional checks.

```typescript
// GOOD: Functional check (parseable)
const submitButton = page.locator('text=Submit');
expect(submitButton).toBeVisible();

// GOOD: Visual check (screenshot)
await page.screenshot({ path: 'dashboard.png', fullPage: true });
```

